✅ Option 1: Use PowerShell (Windows built-in)

PowerShell has [Convert]::ToBase64String() and [Convert]::FromBase64String().

Encode file (local → pod):

[convert]::ToBase64String((Get-Content -path .\image.png -Encoding byte)) |
oc exec -i my-pod -- sh -c "base64 -d > /tmp/image.png"

✅ Option 2: Use Git Bash or WSL

If you have Git Bash or Windows Subsystem for Linux (WSL) installed, you can use base64 just like on Linux:

base64 ./image.png | oc exec -i my-pod -- sh -c 'base64 -d > /tmp/image.png'

✅ Option 3: Use tar + oc exec (works everywhere)

Instead of base64, package files into a tar stream and unpack inside the pod:

Copy a single file:

tar cf - ./config.yaml | oc exec -i my-pod -- tar xf - -C /tmp


Copy a directory:

tar cf - ./mydata | oc exec -i my-pod -- tar xf - -C /app
